1
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,799
Thank you, Tang Mi.

2
00:01:04,428 --> 00:01:06,040
Boss. Boss, I'm sorry!

3
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:07,489
Do you know that for every six minutes you're late,

4
00:01:07,489 --> 00:01:10,167
the world stops turning for six minutes?

5
00:01:10,167 --> 00:01:14,799
I'm so sorry, Boss. Why don't we have breakfast first?

6
00:01:26,500 --> 00:01:29,842
[Xiao Guang is late for six minutes]

7
00:01:36,292 --> 00:01:37,584
Boss, I'm really sorry.

8
00:01:37,584 --> 00:01:39,259
I won't be late again.

9
00:01:44,209 --> 00:01:45,876
Here's your schedule for today.

10
00:01:45,876 --> 00:01:48,209
Lily has arranged some appearances for you.

11
00:01:48,209 --> 00:01:50,792
She knows you don't like doing shows.

12
00:01:50,792 --> 00:01:55,271
So, our strategy is to promote the movie, and restore your image!

13
00:01:55,271 --> 00:01:58,500
As you know, your recent news hasn't been great.

14
00:01:58,500 --> 00:01:59,792
But it's okay!

15
00:01:59,792 --> 00:02:04,459
We just need to stay positive, kind, and warm. That's all.

16
00:02:04,459 --> 00:02:05,876
Hello, everyone, I'm Bai Yin Mo.

17
00:02:05,876 --> 00:02:06,999
- Hello, Chef Fred.
- Hello.

18
00:02:06,999 --> 00:02:08,522
- Thank you for having me today.
- No problem.

19
00:02:08,522 --> 00:02:10,999
- So, you're here to promote a new movie?
- Yes.

20
00:02:10,999 --> 00:02:13,292
I'm here to promote my new film, "Operation Dawn."

21
00:02:13,292 --> 00:02:14,709
I hope everyone supports it.

22
00:02:14,709 --> 00:02:16,042
All right, everyone, show your support.

23
00:02:16,042 --> 00:02:19,676
Let me ask you. Do you have any cooking experience?

24
00:02:20,584 --> 00:02:21,834
I don't cook.

25
00:02:21,834 --> 00:02:23,056
I got it. Don't worry.

26
00:02:23,056 --> 00:02:26,751
Let me tell you. Today's dish is a classic.

27
00:02:26,751 --> 00:02:28,792
It's white wine clams.

28
00:02:28,792 --> 00:02:32,292
First, get the clams ready.

29
00:02:32,292 --> 00:02:35,467
Once they're ready, we'll place them over there.

30
00:02:36,792 --> 00:02:38,292
Pour some white wine

31
00:02:38,292 --> 00:02:42,134
and it turns into white wine clams.

32
00:02:43,083 --> 00:02:45,459
Right? Did I get that wrong?

33
00:02:45,459 --> 00:02:46,867
No.

34
00:02:46,867 --> 00:02:47,885
You're funny.

35
00:02:47,885 --> 00:02:49,834
It's pretty funny, right?

36
00:02:49,834 --> 00:02:53,125
So after this, we'll start cooking.

37
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:54,999
Come on.

38
00:02:54,999 --> 00:02:57,967
What do we need when making white wine clams?

39
00:02:59,584 --> 00:03:00,993
White wine.

40
00:03:00,993 --> 00:03:02,459
You're familiar with it, right?

41
00:03:02,459 --> 00:03:04,999
White wine. Bai Yin Mo.

42
00:03:04,999 --> 00:03:06,542
You know wine well, don't you?

43
00:03:06,542 --> 00:03:09,792
So, when making white wine clams, white wine is the key.

44
00:03:09,792 --> 00:03:10,834
But don't worry.

45
00:03:10,834 --> 00:03:14,334
When we cook it over high heat,

46
00:03:14,334 --> 00:03:17,224
the alcohol will burn off, and there will be none left.

47
00:03:17,224 --> 00:03:20,050
After you eat it later, you can still drive.

48
00:03:21,042 --> 00:03:23,999
Just kidding. All right?

49
00:03:23,999 --> 00:03:27,417
After we prepare the onions,

50
00:03:27,417 --> 00:03:29,584
we'll move on to the garlic.

51
00:03:29,584 --> 00:03:32,459
It's perfect for home cooking.

52
00:03:32,459 --> 00:03:35,483
When it comes to home cooking, your mom will cook it for you.

53
00:03:35,483 --> 00:03:37,792
You can cook it for friends, too.

54
00:03:37,792 --> 00:03:38,999
Let me ask you.

55
00:03:38,999 --> 00:03:42,925
When it comes to making friends, what do you look for?

56
00:03:43,626 --> 00:03:46,999
It's okay. My mom used to tell me this.

57
00:03:46,999 --> 00:03:49,134
We need to be mindful when making friends.

58
00:03:49,751 --> 00:03:51,751
Watch out for the little things.

59
00:03:51,751 --> 00:03:52,918
For example, sometimes,

60
00:03:52,918 --> 00:03:56,542
when you want to grab something, you'll tell them to grab it for you.

61
00:03:56,542 --> 00:03:59,342
When they turn around, they might turn like this.

62
00:04:00,918 --> 00:04:01,999
Do you know what that means?

63
00:04:01,999 --> 00:04:04,334
He must have been arrested before.

64
00:04:04,334 --> 00:04:06,459
Or maybe he has been handcuffed.

65
00:04:06,459 --> 00:04:07,918
Got it?

66
00:04:07,918 --> 00:04:09,759
You got it, right?

67
00:04:12,167 --> 00:04:14,999
Boss, calm down!

68
00:04:14,999 --> 00:04:17,634
- Calm down.
- Darn you!

69
00:04:28,626 --> 00:04:30,426
[Bai Yin Mo joins the battle]

70
00:04:31,709 --> 00:04:32,925
[Unbeatable Punch]

71
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,799
[Mission failed, you blasted the chef]

72
00:04:54,125 --> 00:04:56,751
