74
00:05:00,626 --> 00:05:03,000
♫ The vulnerability I long to embrace ♫

75
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,876
♫ Is buried deep inside ♫

76
00:05:05,876 --> 00:05:09,709
♫ Under the moon's radiant glow, dreams surge and swell ♫

77
00:05:09,709 --> 00:05:12,083
♫ Waiting for a reason to run wild ♫

78
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:17,925
♫ Can you walk with me for a while without saying a word? ♫

79
00:05:19,209 --> 00:05:22,250
♫ Follow the neon lights into the night ♫

80
00:05:22,250 --> 00:05:25,375
♫ I try to find you every night ♫

81
00:05:25,375 --> 00:05:30,250
♫ What must I do to see through that distant line? ♫

82
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:35,417
♫ I want to feel the wind full force ♫

83
00:05:35,417 --> 00:05:38,500
♫ My lonely soul begins to shake ♫

84
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:43,417
♫ What can we trust to forever endure? ♫

85
00:05:43,417 --> 00:05:47,918
♫ I want to bring my freedom forth, and take your hand ♫

86
00:05:47,918 --> 00:05:53,375
♫ When the warmth finally seeps into every memory's corner ♫

87
00:05:53,375 --> 00:06:01,634
♫ The past was never wrong, having us is enough forever ♫

88
00:06:09,999 --> 00:06:13,799
[Breeze by the Sea]

89
00:07:22,792 --> 00:07:24,925
You can rest over there.

90
00:07:25,584 --> 00:07:27,334
It's nice to feel the breeze.

91
00:07:27,334 --> 00:07:29,134
The view is beautiful, too.

92
00:07:31,422 --> 00:07:32,797
He can't rest.

93
00:07:32,797 --> 00:07:34,999
Mom, did you hear what I said?

94
00:07:34,999 --> 00:07:36,500
I don't want to act anymore.

95
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,800
I want to go back to school.

96
00:07:39,542 --> 00:07:42,459
If he can't make money, what value does he have?

97
00:07:42,459 --> 00:07:43,918
I don't want to rest.

98
00:07:43,918 --> 00:07:45,542
I want to go back to the set.

99
00:07:45,542 --> 00:07:47,000
I want to make money.

100
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,050
I have to make money for them.

101
00:07:49,959 --> 00:07:51,799
Bai Yin Mo, aren't you embarrassed?

102
00:08:30,857 --> 00:08:32,197
It's okay.

103
00:08:32,197 --> 00:08:33,799
Let's go home.

104
00:09:37,989 --> 00:09:40,697
Last time at the police station, I didn't speak very nicely to your artist.

105
00:09:40,697 --> 00:09:42,512
I'm sorry about that.

106
00:09:42,512 --> 00:09:43,771
It's okay.

107
00:09:43,771 --> 00:09:45,859
You didn't call just to apologize, did you?

108
00:09:45,859 --> 00:09:47,859
Get to the point.

109
00:09:47,859 --> 00:09:49,483
You really live up to your reputation, Lily.

110
00:09:49,483 --> 00:09:52,400
Last time, we caught Tang Mi sneaking in and out of Bai Yin Mo's place

111
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,400
in the middle of the night.

112
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:59,199
Does your company know about the relationship status between the two of them?

113
00:10:00,399 --> 00:10:02,399
What do you think?

114
00:10:02,399 --> 00:10:04,359
That means...

115
00:10:04,359 --> 00:10:06,534
you're acknowledging their relationship, right?

116
00:10:08,483 --> 00:10:12,617
I never meddle in our artists' personal affairs.

117
00:10:14,399 --> 00:10:17,034
Lily, I got the coffee you asked for.

118
00:10:18,399 --> 00:10:20,067
What's wrong?

119
00:10:20,067 --> 00:10:23,617
Watch the news later and you'll know.

120
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:26,984
Latest entertainment news.

121
00:10:26,984 --> 00:10:34,067
Famous actor Bai Yin Mo is rumored to be in a relationship with his junior, Tang Mi.

122
00:10:34,067 --> 00:10:38,734
Tang Mi was spotted driving Bai Yin Mo's car back to his place at night.

123
00:10:38,734 --> 00:10:40,399
She didn't leave for quite a while,

124
00:10:40,399 --> 00:10:43,234
leading to speculation that the two might already be living together.

125
00:10:43,234 --> 00:10:48,159
So far, the management company has not responded.

126
00:10:53,234 --> 00:10:54,970
Lily, I'm sorry.

127
00:10:54,970 --> 00:10:56,650
I was really tired that day,

128
00:10:56,650 --> 00:11:01,742
so I asked Tang Mi to help drive the car back to Yin Mo's place.

129
00:11:05,734 --> 00:11:09,399
Tang Mi, sorry. I fell asleep.

130
00:11:09,399 --> 00:11:10,734
It's fine.

131
00:11:10,734 --> 00:11:12,399
They're serving late-night snacks now.

132
00:11:12,399 --> 00:11:14,483
Snacks?

133
00:11:14,483 --> 00:11:17,617
Wait, we haven't finished shooting this scene?

134
00:11:18,399 --> 00:11:19,883
What do you want to eat? I'll grab something for you.

135
00:11:19,883 --> 00:11:21,732
There's some hot tea on the table.

136
00:11:21,732 --> 00:11:23,565
It's okay. I'm not hungry.

137
00:11:23,565 --> 00:11:25,192
You should go rest.

138
00:11:25,192 --> 00:11:26,575
There's one more scene left.

139
00:11:26,575 --> 00:11:28,283
I can go home by myself.

140
00:11:29,276 --> 00:11:30,933
I can't.

141
00:11:30,933 --> 00:11:34,199
I still have to drive Yin Mo's car back to his place later.

142
00:11:35,567 --> 00:11:37,650
How about I drive it back for you?

143
00:11:37,650 --> 00:11:39,742
You can get more rest.

144
00:11:40,399 --> 00:11:42,609
Are you sure?

145
00:11:42,609 --> 00:11:44,575
Yes, I'm off tomorrow anyway.

146
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,775
After you park the car,

147
00:12:10,775 --> 00:12:13,749
leave the car key in the entryway.

148
00:12:13,749 --> 00:12:16,234
Remember. You have to be quiet.

149
00:12:16,234 --> 00:12:18,199
Don't wake him up.

150
00:12:49,399 --> 00:12:51,534
It's so soft.

151
00:13:00,525 --> 00:13:04,109
I had no idea it would be photographed and turn into such a big deal.

152
00:13:04,109 --> 00:13:05,234
Let's issue a press release!

153
00:13:05,234 --> 00:13:06,859
Let's explain it with a press release, can we?

154
00:13:06,859 --> 00:13:09,907
This rumor came at the right time.

155
00:13:09,907 --> 00:13:13,159
It perfectly covers up the incident of him hitting someone.

156
00:13:13,984 --> 00:13:15,499
The audience has a short memory.

157
00:13:15,499 --> 00:13:19,848
In a while, everyone will forget about all this.

158
00:13:19,848 --> 00:13:23,276
Plus, we can use the reality show

159
00:13:23,276 --> 00:13:27,900
to give him a complete makeover and a brand-new image.

160
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:32,734
However, if Yin Mo finds out, he'll be really mad.

161
00:13:32,734 --> 00:13:36,367
There's no need to tell him. He doesn't read the news anyway.

162
00:13:57,476 --> 00:13:58,908
Hi, I'm Tang Mi.

163
00:13:58,908 --> 00:14:01,399
I have an appointment with Sun Sun.

164
00:14:02,559 --> 00:14:04,599
Sun Sun, Tang Mi is here.

165
00:14:04,599 --> 00:14:06,599
Tang Mi, this way, please.

166
00:14:06,599 --> 00:14:09,642
We've already prepared your favorite snacks.

167
00:14:09,642 --> 00:14:11,683
Thank you.

168
00:14:11,683 --> 00:14:13,731
What do you want to do today?

169
00:14:13,731 --> 00:14:16,142
I'll go with scalp care today.

170
00:14:16,142 --> 00:14:18,476
All right, Tang Mi. Please wait a moment.

171
00:14:18,476 --> 00:14:21,518
Well, shouldn't I start calling you Mrs. Bai now?

172
00:14:21,518 --> 00:14:22,599
Stop joking around.

173
00:14:22,599 --> 00:14:24,399
You two are a great match.

174
00:14:38,698 --> 00:14:40,765
Tang Mi, you're finally in the spotlight.

175
00:14:40,765 --> 00:14:42,309
You're all over the news.

176
00:14:42,309 --> 00:14:44,015
Even my colleagues know who you are.

177
00:14:44,015 --> 00:14:45,632
Looks like you're going to be famous.

178
00:14:45,632 --> 00:14:47,424
I saw the news, too.

179
00:14:47,424 --> 00:14:50,351
I finally have a celebrity friend.

180
00:14:50,351 --> 00:14:53,399
I have a celebrity friend.

181
00:16:48,059 --> 00:16:50,059
Isn't it fixed?

182
00:16:50,059 --> 00:16:52,234
You were so fierce before.

183
00:17:34,799 --> 00:17:36,599
What is it?

184
00:17:37,384 --> 00:17:38,799
Don't you know what time it is now?

185
00:17:38,799 --> 00:17:41,009
You have your music on so loud.

186
00:17:41,009 --> 00:17:44,309
- It's only a little past ten.
- I go to sleep by ten.

187
00:17:45,149 --> 00:17:47,599
- I'll turn it off later.
- Turn it off now.

188
00:17:59,898 --> 00:18:02,309
Is that a photo of your grandma?

189
00:18:03,426 --> 00:18:05,017
Yes.

190
00:18:07,099 --> 00:18:08,850
Is this you as a kid?

191
00:18:09,799 --> 00:18:12,100
You were cuter as a kid.

192
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:15,642
Hey, I didn't say you could come in.

193
00:18:17,358 --> 00:18:19,850
Do you like to read?

194
00:18:21,718 --> 00:18:24,259
You live in Kinmen now. Why do you still read about Kinmen?

195
00:18:24,259 --> 00:18:26,191
It's none of your business.

196
00:18:26,191 --> 00:18:27,342
Wait.

197
00:18:27,342 --> 00:18:29,799
You can't just barge into a girl's room at midnight.

198
00:18:29,799 --> 00:18:32,683
- What are you even doing?
- Didn't you say it's still early?

199
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:38,892
So, you don't read, but you like to draw?

200
00:18:42,134 --> 00:18:46,057
You use advertising paint to paint oil paintings.

201
00:18:46,057 --> 00:18:47,600
Colored markers.

202
00:18:56,997 --> 00:18:59,132
Are you just looking for something to do?

203
00:18:59,132 --> 00:19:01,559
- What do you want?
- Nothing.

204
00:19:09,048 --> 00:19:11,559
Is this the legendary love charm?

205
00:19:13,081 --> 00:19:17,142
If you really want to stay with your grandma, you should throw it away.

206
00:19:19,542 --> 00:19:20,999
You know nothing.

207
00:19:20,999 --> 00:19:24,709
This love charm's red thread connects me and my grandma.

208
00:19:24,709 --> 00:19:26,125
So? Is there anything else?

209
00:19:26,125 --> 00:19:28,676
Nothing. What else?

210
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,967
What a weirdo.

211
00:19:37,459 --> 00:19:40,800
Why does it look like a radish to me?

212
00:19:41,542 --> 00:19:43,500
Why do I feel that it looks like a winter melon?

213
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:45,801
I still think it looks more like a radish.

214
00:19:45,801 --> 00:19:48,417
Or are we going to cook the radish and winter melon together?

215
00:19:48,417 --> 00:19:51,334
How can you pair radish with winter melon? They don't go well together.

216
00:19:51,334 --> 00:19:52,999
I just...

217
00:19:52,999 --> 00:19:55,718
That's a daikon. What are you two doing?

218
00:19:57,584 --> 00:19:59,167
We don't know what you like to eat,

219
00:19:59,167 --> 00:20:03,000
so Grandma suggested finding clues from your work photos.

220
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:06,709
If it is called a work photo, do you think I'll eat it?

221
00:20:06,709 --> 00:20:09,876
You see. I told you it was all in vain.

222
00:20:09,876 --> 00:20:11,667
So, what do you want to eat?

223
00:20:11,667 --> 00:20:13,292
Just cook it like before.

224
00:20:13,292 --> 00:20:15,509
Before?

225
00:20:20,334 --> 00:20:22,634
I want to eat your cooking.

226
00:20:34,042 --> 00:20:36,342
Does it taste good?

227
00:20:37,959 --> 00:20:39,925
It's so delicious.

228
00:20:40,999 --> 00:20:42,925
Is it really that good?

229
00:20:44,876 --> 00:20:45,999
How about this?

230
00:20:45,999 --> 00:20:49,967
Next time, I'll make boiled eggs for you to eat.

231
00:21:10,626 --> 00:21:11,626
Good morning.

232
00:21:11,626 --> 00:21:13,999
Morning.

233
00:21:13,999 --> 00:21:15,718
Boiled eggs?

234
00:21:16,918 --> 00:21:18,626
I got drunk last night.

235
00:21:18,626 --> 00:21:21,709
I heard it was you who carried me back.

236
00:21:21,709 --> 00:21:22,999
I'm really sorry.

237
00:21:22,999 --> 00:21:25,009
Next time, you carry me.

238
00:21:25,626 --> 00:21:27,467
You owe me one.

239
00:21:28,334 --> 00:21:31,384
Sure. No problem.

240
00:21:33,709 --> 00:21:35,925
It's hot. Let me help you.

241
00:21:37,292 --> 00:21:39,417
- What is that?
- He cooked it himself.

242
00:21:39,417 --> 00:21:41,779
- I can tell.
- Is this enough?

243
00:21:41,779 --> 00:21:42,999
I'm used to it.

244
00:21:42,999 --> 00:21:44,876
Grandma, you don't need to worry about him.

245
00:21:44,876 --> 00:21:47,467
He only eats the healthiest food.

246
00:21:53,876 --> 00:21:55,551
He eats raw food.

247
00:21:59,099 --> 00:22:01,842
My nutritionist said
that this is the right doneness for me.

248
00:22:02,959 --> 00:22:05,342
I see.

249
00:22:08,999 --> 00:22:11,967
- Don't you guys want to eat?
- Let's eat.

250
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:27,925
Mr. Bai, you must be joking.

251
00:22:28,959 --> 00:22:31,000
I'm just joking.

252
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,799
Just joking.

253
00:22:33,751 --> 00:22:35,883
I peeled this for you.

254
00:22:37,507 --> 00:22:39,342
Did you wash your hands?

255
00:22:40,131 --> 00:22:42,209
I washed my hands.

256
00:22:42,209 --> 00:22:43,900
If you don't want to eat, that's fine.

257
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:46,300
Just joking.

258
00:22:49,626 --> 00:22:51,842
Just joking.

259
00:22:53,375 --> 00:22:55,292
I'm just joking.

260
00:22:55,292 --> 00:22:56,834
This is really delicious.

261
00:22:56,834 --> 00:22:58,751
- Grandma, do you understand what I mean?
- I understand.

262
00:22:58,751 --> 00:23:00,799
If it's good, eat more.

263
00:23:03,542 --> 00:23:06,009
I'm eating. I'm not joking.

264
00:23:13,584 --> 00:23:15,296
Yin Mo.

265
00:23:15,296 --> 00:23:18,982
I know you pack every day full with work.

266
00:23:18,982 --> 00:23:20,164
However, this time,

267
00:23:20,164 --> 00:23:22,467
you're going to Kinmen with a half-vacation mindset.

268
00:23:23,707 --> 00:23:26,034
You should try to relax as much as possible.

269
00:23:26,034 --> 00:23:28,242
Xiao Guang said you fainted in Kinmen.

270
00:23:28,242 --> 00:23:29,742
Are you okay?

271
00:23:29,742 --> 00:23:31,626
I'm fine.

272
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:38,199
I'll handle it. What if you fall?

273
00:23:38,199 --> 00:23:39,199
How do you use this?

274
00:23:39,199 --> 00:23:43,250
Just roll and pull it. It should be the same height as that.

275
00:23:44,409 --> 00:23:45,867
Be careful.

276
00:23:45,867 --> 00:23:47,999
Be careful.

277
00:23:49,199 --> 00:23:52,375
- Like this?
- A little higher.

278
00:23:53,034 --> 00:23:55,334
Align it. Thank you.

279
00:24:06,909 --> 00:24:09,709
What do you think about the reality show?

280
00:24:17,034 --> 00:24:18,999
All right. I'll take it.

281
00:24:20,283 --> 00:24:22,659
Are you still having trouble adjusting over there?

282
00:24:22,659 --> 00:24:26,500
Do you need anything? I can send you some stuff from Taipei.

283
00:24:27,199 --> 00:24:30,199
I want to continue experiencing life in Kinmen.

284
00:24:30,199 --> 00:24:31,933
Send me the proposal once it's done.

285
00:24:31,933 --> 00:24:33,209
That's it.

286
00:24:43,367 --> 00:24:44,775
Mr. Bai.

287
00:24:44,775 --> 00:24:45,799
Sorry.

288
00:24:45,799 --> 00:24:50,042
I think I heard you said you want to stay in Kinmen to experience life.

289
00:24:51,199 --> 00:24:53,584
Do you have time later?

290
00:25:10,318 --> 00:25:11,490
Nuo Nuo!

291
00:25:11,490 --> 00:25:12,867
Nuo Nuo!

292
00:25:12,867 --> 00:25:14,118
Nuo Nuo!

293
00:25:14,118 --> 00:25:15,584
Nuo Nuo!

294
00:25:17,784 --> 00:25:19,365
Did you guys call me?

295
00:25:19,365 --> 00:25:21,118
Why do you have your music so loud?

296
00:25:21,118 --> 00:25:22,532
Are you hard of hearing?

297
00:25:22,532 --> 00:25:24,541
Is it really that loud?

298
00:25:24,541 --> 00:25:27,409
Mr. Bai is going with me to the market to buy groceries.

299
00:25:27,409 --> 00:25:28,674
He said he wants to...

300
00:25:28,674 --> 00:25:30,407
Wants to what? No way.

301
00:25:30,407 --> 00:25:32,341
No way for what?

302
00:25:32,341 --> 00:25:34,784
For letting him cook.

303
00:25:34,784 --> 00:25:36,951
I'm afraid you'll blow up our kitchen.

304
00:25:36,951 --> 00:25:39,999
I just want your grandma to take me to experience life in Kinmen.

305
00:25:41,242 --> 00:25:43,591
That's good. No problem. Take care.

306
00:25:43,591 --> 00:25:45,909
- Then we'll head out. Bye.
- Come back early.

307
00:25:45,909 --> 00:25:47,542
Okay.

308
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:35,547
- Grandma.
- What's wrong?

309
00:26:35,547 --> 00:26:37,116
I forgot to bring my wallet.

310
00:26:37,116 --> 00:26:39,397
It's okay. I have money.

311
00:26:39,397 --> 00:26:42,076
I'm going out with a woman, of course I'll pay.

312
00:26:42,076 --> 00:26:45,042
- I'll go get it. I'll be back soon.
- All right.

313
00:27:12,430 --> 00:27:13,999
Sir.

314
00:27:18,739 --> 00:27:20,330
Sir.

315
00:27:23,958 --> 00:27:25,667
Li Hai.

316
00:27:34,316 --> 00:27:36,225
Police station?

317
00:27:36,225 --> 00:27:38,364
I'm at the Sea Breeze Guesthouse.

318
00:27:38,364 --> 00:27:40,175
There's a stranger collapsed here

319
00:27:40,175 --> 00:27:42,292
and he's seriously injured.

320
00:27:47,534 --> 00:27:49,334
At the scene...

321
00:30:23,325 --> 00:30:26,415
I have a strange fate with police stations, huh.

322
00:30:26,415 --> 00:30:28,626
What's up? Kinmen branch.

323
00:30:42,184 --> 00:30:43,309
Mr. Bai Yin Mo.

324
00:30:43,309 --> 00:30:46,599
Can you describe what happened at that time?

325
00:30:46,599 --> 00:30:48,848
I was supposed to go out

326
00:30:48,848 --> 00:30:50,599
to buy groceries with Ms. Shu Man.

327
00:30:50,599 --> 00:30:52,309
I realized I had forgotten my wallet,

328
00:30:52,309 --> 00:30:54,267
so I rushed back to the guesthouse.

329
00:30:54,267 --> 00:30:58,567
When I got back to the guesthouse,
I saw an injured man lying on the ground.

330
00:30:59,965 --> 00:31:01,400
Sir.

331
00:31:05,434 --> 00:31:06,875
Hai Nuo.

332
00:31:06,875 --> 00:31:08,599
I really don't feel well.

333
00:31:08,599 --> 00:31:11,399
I've forgotten so many things.

334
00:31:12,731 --> 00:31:14,584
I only remember

335
00:31:14,584 --> 00:31:18,900
I was at the guesthouse to ask about accommodation.

336
00:31:20,434 --> 00:31:24,900
A stranger grabbed a knife from the side...

337
00:31:25,599 --> 00:31:27,483
and suddenly attacked me.

338
00:31:28,892 --> 00:31:31,599
I didn't react in time.

339
00:31:31,599 --> 00:31:33,817
I was knocked unconscious.

340
00:31:34,725 --> 00:31:36,149
Mr. Chen Da Wu.

341
00:31:36,149 --> 00:31:38,525
Could you describe the situation at that time?

342
00:31:40,309 --> 00:31:41,599
Sorry.

343
00:31:41,599 --> 00:31:42,932
I haven't been back in a long time.

344
00:31:42,932 --> 00:31:44,991
I'm a bit allergic.

345
00:31:44,991 --> 00:31:46,476
I just returned to Kinmen.

346
00:31:46,476 --> 00:31:49,934
On my way home, I passed by Sea Breeze Guesthouse.

347
00:31:49,934 --> 00:31:53,142
I haven't been back in so long, so I wanted to go in and take a look.

348
00:31:53,142 --> 00:31:56,767
When I entered the yard, I saw a man standing there sneakily.

349
00:31:56,767 --> 00:31:59,399
I approached to ask what he wanted.

350
00:32:00,226 --> 00:32:02,026
He suddenly attacked me.

351
00:32:03,476 --> 00:32:05,142
I do have some training.

352
00:32:05,142 --> 00:32:07,599
So... I might've hit him too hard.

353
00:32:07,599 --> 00:32:09,599
After I called the police,

354
00:32:09,599 --> 00:32:12,142
I wanted to go in and see what was happening.

355
00:32:12,142 --> 00:32:13,809
I saw that guy.

356
00:32:13,809 --> 00:32:16,599
The knife-wielding man I subdued.

357
00:32:16,599 --> 00:32:18,809
I was worried he had accomplices,

358
00:32:18,809 --> 00:32:21,567
so I picked up his knife.

359
00:32:22,309 --> 00:32:26,067
After checking the first floor, I went to the second floor.

360
00:32:27,085 --> 00:32:30,252
And I ran into the man I had subdued.

361
00:32:30,252 --> 00:32:31,900
That man...

362
00:32:32,725 --> 00:32:34,399
That man...

363
00:32:37,392 --> 00:32:39,567
- Clearly looked like a bad guy.
- Looked like a bad guy.

364
00:32:41,033 --> 00:32:44,467
I really had no idea what was going on.

365
00:32:44,467 --> 00:32:46,066
What were you doing at the time?

366
00:32:46,066 --> 00:32:48,642
Collecting laundry, folding clothes,

367
00:32:48,642 --> 00:32:49,975
and listening to music.

368
00:32:52,358 --> 00:32:57,399
Officer, may I ask what exactly happened?

369
00:33:31,507 --> 00:33:33,109
Da Wu!

370
00:33:37,608 --> 00:33:39,599
Why didn't you tell us you were coming back?

371
00:33:39,599 --> 00:33:41,142
I wanted to give you a surprise.

372
00:33:41,142 --> 00:33:44,192
A surprise? That's quite a surprise.

373
00:33:45,731 --> 00:33:48,408
By the way, that's Bai Yin Mo.

374
00:33:48,408 --> 00:33:50,073
He stays at our guesthouse.

375
00:33:50,073 --> 00:33:51,300
Mr. Bai.

376
00:33:51,300 --> 00:33:54,318
This is Chen Da Wu, the village chief's son.

377
00:33:56,199 --> 00:33:59,215
By the way, I just heard from the police

378
00:33:59,215 --> 00:34:01,149
that the criminal is a wanted suspect.

379
00:34:01,149 --> 00:34:02,929
He specializes in robbery and assault.

380
00:34:02,929 --> 00:34:04,066
Good thing I was home.

381
00:34:04,066 --> 00:34:05,731
If my grandma was home alone,

382
00:34:05,731 --> 00:34:07,617
it would have been too dangerous.

383
00:34:07,617 --> 00:34:09,224
I'll go back to find your grandma.

384
00:34:09,224 --> 00:34:10,797
I just contacted her.

385
00:34:10,797 --> 00:34:12,608
She went out to buy groceries.

386
00:34:12,608 --> 00:34:14,896
Hai Nuo, I'll go home first. I'll find you and your grandma later.

387
00:34:14,896 --> 00:34:16,692
Okay.

388
00:34:20,557 --> 00:34:21,599
See you later!

389
00:34:21,599 --> 00:34:24,067
- Bye!
- Bye.

390
00:34:27,797 --> 00:34:29,399
Let's go.

391
00:34:32,797 --> 00:34:34,641
Was that your boyfriend?

392
00:34:34,641 --> 00:34:35,896
No.

393
00:34:35,896 --> 00:34:38,683
He's a good friend I grew up with.

394
00:34:38,683 --> 00:34:39,934
We had so much fun as kids.

395
00:34:39,934 --> 00:34:42,724
We'd play hide and seek in the sorghum fields.

396
00:34:42,724 --> 00:34:44,962
We'd go to the beach and play Eagle and Chicks.

397
00:34:44,962 --> 00:34:47,516
At night, we'd catch crabs and roast them to eat.

398
00:34:47,516 --> 00:34:49,984
My childhood was fun, right?

399
00:34:52,100 --> 00:34:54,288
- How dirty.
- Dirty?

400
00:34:54,288 --> 00:34:56,692
How clean was your childhood?

401
00:34:58,434 --> 00:35:00,817
You didn't spend your childhood acting, did you?

402
00:35:01,665 --> 00:35:03,252
Who is that Lin guy?

403
00:35:03,252 --> 00:35:04,896
Is he Xiao Guang's cousin?

404
00:35:04,896 --> 00:35:06,133
He is Xiao Guang's cousin.

405
00:35:06,133 --> 00:35:08,476
His last name is Chen. He's Chen Da Wu.

406
00:35:08,476 --> 00:35:10,615
He's the representative of Kinmen's model students.

407
00:35:10,615 --> 00:35:12,226
He's smart and kind.

408
00:35:12,226 --> 00:35:13,525
Unlike you.

409
00:35:14,267 --> 00:35:15,949
Stop insulting people.

410
00:35:15,949 --> 00:35:17,790
I can tell from your expression.

411
00:35:17,790 --> 00:35:20,145
Listen up, don't bully the people of Kinmen.

412
00:35:20,145 --> 00:35:21,356
I'm not insulting anyone.

413
00:35:21,356 --> 00:35:23,038
Your expression says it all.

414
00:35:23,038 --> 00:35:24,689
Nuo Nuo.

415
00:35:24,689 --> 00:35:26,896
- Nuo Nuo.
- Grandma.

416
00:35:26,896 --> 00:35:29,342
Grandma.

417
00:35:29,342 --> 00:35:31,392
Let me help you.

418
00:35:31,392 --> 00:35:33,371
Let me help you.

419
00:35:33,371 --> 00:35:36,106
Let me carry this, and you can take this.

420
00:35:36,106 --> 00:35:37,758
Be careful.

421
00:35:37,758 --> 00:35:39,899
Grandma, Da Wu is back.

422
00:35:39,899 --> 00:35:41,818
Really?

423
00:35:41,818 --> 00:35:43,900
Where is he now?

424
00:35:43,900 --> 00:35:46,025
I think he's going back to his parents' home.

425
00:35:46,025 --> 00:35:48,734
He should come to find us later.

426
00:35:48,734 --> 00:35:51,359
That's great, he's back. That's wonderful.

427
00:35:51,359 --> 00:35:54,783
We can cook more dishes for him tonight.

428
00:36:00,899 --> 00:36:04,282
This time, we really have to thank Mr. Bai and Da Wu.

429
00:36:04,282 --> 00:36:06,899
Without them, Nuo Nuo
wouldn't have been safe and sound.

430
00:36:06,899 --> 00:36:07,942
Grandma.

431
00:36:07,942 --> 00:36:09,484
Mr. Bai didn't even see the thief

432
00:36:09,484 --> 00:36:11,150
and the thief was already subdued.

433
00:36:11,150 --> 00:36:13,275
Da Wu thought he was the thief,

434
00:36:13,275 --> 00:36:15,692
so he fought with him and pinned him to the floor.

435
00:36:15,692 --> 00:36:16,899
Are you listening to me?

436
00:36:16,899 --> 00:36:18,065
Wait a minute.

437
00:36:18,065 --> 00:36:19,425
What are you posting?

438
00:36:19,425 --> 00:36:20,734
It's done.

439
00:36:20,734 --> 00:36:23,109
Check it out in the group chat.

440
00:36:23,109 --> 00:36:25,326
Let me take a look.

441
00:36:26,282 --> 00:36:29,859
Mr. Bai and Da Wu subdued the criminal together.

442
00:36:29,859 --> 00:36:32,140
Everyone misunderstood Mr. Bai.

443
00:36:32,140 --> 00:36:34,275
He's actually a very nice person.

444
00:36:34,275 --> 00:36:37,699
He even protected Hai Nuo today.

445
00:36:39,965 --> 00:36:41,727
Mr. Bai.

446
00:36:41,727 --> 00:36:43,458
My grandma has cleared your name

447
00:36:43,458 --> 00:36:46,534
from being the public enemy of Kinmen.

448
00:36:47,484 --> 00:36:48,950
Thank you.

449
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:52,899
I'm sorry.

450
00:36:52,899 --> 00:36:54,526
Da Wu isn't here and I keep bothering you.

451
00:36:54,526 --> 00:36:55,899
No worries.

452
00:36:55,899 --> 00:36:59,109
Da Wu is studying abroad, and he's the pride of Kinmen.

453
00:36:59,109 --> 00:37:02,526
As someone who he has respected since he was little,

454
00:37:02,526 --> 00:37:05,367
it's only right for me to help his parents.

455
00:37:06,526 --> 00:37:10,859
He always gets into fights because he was following in your footsteps.

456
00:37:10,859 --> 00:37:13,275
Has Shun Hua gotten into another fight recently?

457
00:37:13,275 --> 00:37:15,776
Stop talking about those fights.

458
00:37:15,776 --> 00:37:18,576
Shun Hua has turned over a new leaf now.

459
00:37:18,576 --> 00:37:20,899
He has become a warmhearted guy.

460
00:37:20,899 --> 00:37:22,484
Look.

461
00:37:22,484 --> 00:37:24,859
Look at our Kinmen elementary and middle school's track team.

462
00:37:24,859 --> 00:37:26,899
They've broken records. Look.

463
00:37:26,899 --> 00:37:28,289
What's so special about that?

464
00:37:28,289 --> 00:37:30,816
- There?
- Yes, thank you.

465
00:37:30,816 --> 00:37:34,859
Da Wu has been the best since Kinmen High School was founded.

466
00:37:34,859 --> 00:37:37,699
He graduated at the top of a medical school.

467
00:37:50,942 --> 00:37:52,692
My son!

468
00:37:52,692 --> 00:37:54,734
Mom.

469
00:37:54,734 --> 00:37:56,634
Why didn't you tell us you were coming back?

470
00:37:56,634 --> 00:37:58,150
I could've asked your dad to pick you up.

471
00:37:58,150 --> 00:38:00,159
There's no need for that.

472
00:38:01,465 --> 00:38:02,598
Hi, ma'am.

473
00:38:02,598 --> 00:38:04,200
Zhi Ting.

474
00:38:05,442 --> 00:38:08,034
Shun Hua.

475
00:38:13,275 --> 00:38:14,909
It has been a while.

476
00:38:17,150 --> 00:38:19,899
Da Wu, you're getting handsome.

477
00:38:19,899 --> 00:38:23,998
- You flattered me.
- Not only is Da Wu handsome, but he's also smart.

478
00:38:23,998 --> 00:38:26,631
He speaks fluent English overseas.

479
00:38:26,631 --> 00:38:29,697
Unlike me. When a foreigner asks me for directions,

480
00:38:29,697 --> 00:38:30,965
I become mute.

481
00:38:30,965 --> 00:38:33,783
Shun Hua, let me tell you. English is very simple.

482
00:38:33,783 --> 00:38:36,282
You only need to learn three sentences.

483
00:38:36,282 --> 00:38:38,998
When you buy something, you ask, "How much?"

484
00:38:38,998 --> 00:38:42,932
When you want to haggle, you say, "Too much."

485
00:38:42,932 --> 00:38:45,359
And when you say goodbye, "Thank you very much."

486
00:38:45,359 --> 00:38:46,581
I know this one.

487
00:38:46,581 --> 00:38:48,999
- Thank you very much!
- See? Isn't it easy?

488
00:38:48,999 --> 00:38:51,557
All right. My handsome son is finally back.

489
00:38:51,557 --> 00:38:54,651
Let me take him inside to see my husband first.

490
00:38:54,651 --> 00:38:57,075
Thank you very much.

491
00:39:00,776 --> 00:39:03,280
Why is the paint on our door peeling?

492
00:39:03,280 --> 00:39:05,442
It's your dad's masterpiece.

493
00:39:05,442 --> 00:39:10,326
He got drunk and couldn't find the key, so he used a rock to knock on the door.

494
00:39:12,067 --> 00:39:13,899
Why stick this here?

495
00:39:13,899 --> 00:39:16,699
Once, he got drunk and went to the bathroom at night.

496
00:39:21,445 --> 00:39:25,366
He actually opened it and peed inside.

497
00:39:25,366 --> 00:39:27,531
You know that day is coming soon.

498
00:39:27,531 --> 00:39:29,274
Your dad is getting a bit gloomy.

499
00:39:29,274 --> 00:39:31,965
Lately, he has been having nightmares.

500
00:39:31,965 --> 00:39:34,917
You need to talk to him properly this time.

501
00:39:34,917 --> 00:39:37,742
Don't let him drink so much that he risks his life.

502
00:39:38,734 --> 00:39:40,917
- All right.
- Dad.

503
00:39:40,917 --> 00:39:42,230
Our son just got back.

504
00:39:42,230 --> 00:39:43,734
You haven't even offered him any drinks

505
00:39:43,734 --> 00:39:45,941
and you keep talking about random stuff.

506
00:39:45,941 --> 00:39:47,272
Da Wu, sit down.

507
00:39:47,272 --> 00:39:48,783
Have some tea.

508
00:39:56,656 --> 00:39:59,536
Dad, do you still drink a lot?

509
00:39:59,536 --> 00:40:01,163
Just a little.

510
00:40:01,163 --> 00:40:03,159
It helps me sleep better at night.

511
00:40:05,262 --> 00:40:08,899
Hong Hui Fang, aren't you concerned about how he has been doing abroad?

512
00:40:08,899 --> 00:40:10,739
Of course I am.

513
00:40:10,739 --> 00:40:13,884
He said he's doing okay. Healthy and safe.

514
00:40:13,884 --> 00:40:16,575
Did you tell him not to send us money anymore?

515
00:40:16,575 --> 00:40:19,299
He should save it for himself to buy a house and get married.

516
00:40:19,299 --> 00:40:22,509
I've told him many times, but he insists on giving it to me, what can I do?

517
00:40:22,509 --> 00:40:24,509
Do you know how long he plans to stay this time?

518
00:40:24,509 --> 00:40:26,888
Why don't you ask him yourself? Why do you keep asking me?

519
00:40:26,888 --> 00:40:29,100
He's sitting right across from you.

520
00:40:33,299 --> 00:40:34,509
Dad.

521
00:40:34,509 --> 00:40:38,851
I came back early to Kinmen this time because I wanted to stay longer.

522
00:40:39,967 --> 00:40:41,342
Staying longer isn't the issue.

523
00:40:41,342 --> 00:40:43,300
The question is how long you'll stay.

524
00:40:43,300 --> 00:40:44,795
You need to figure that out.

525
00:40:44,795 --> 00:40:46,926
Your age now

526
00:40:46,926 --> 00:40:50,299
is the prime time for a man to make a career.

527
00:40:50,299 --> 00:40:52,099
You understand, right?

528
00:40:55,035 --> 00:40:57,099
Dad, let me take this call.

529
00:40:59,092 --> 00:41:00,518
Hello.

530
00:41:21,342 --> 00:41:23,967
Your grandma's cooking is still more delicious.

531
00:41:23,967 --> 00:41:25,800
Many people are selling Chinese dishes out there,

532
00:41:25,800 --> 00:41:29,300
but only your grandma's cooking fits my taste.

533
00:41:29,300 --> 00:41:30,365
Come on.

534
00:41:30,365 --> 00:41:33,299
You used to mooch off my family for years.

535
00:41:33,299 --> 00:41:37,059
That flavor must be etched deep into your soul.

536
00:41:39,467 --> 00:41:41,342
My grandma always says

537
00:41:41,342 --> 00:41:43,299
that she never thought you would become a doctor.

538
00:41:43,299 --> 00:41:45,299
She thought you'd be an athlete,

539
00:41:45,299 --> 00:41:48,299
a bodyguard, or something like that.

540
00:41:48,299 --> 00:41:51,099
After all, you've loved fighting since you were little.

541
00:41:54,176 --> 00:41:56,134
I did think about it.

542
00:41:56,134 --> 00:41:58,675
That's why I became a doctor.

543
00:41:58,675 --> 00:42:00,800
To hurt people and then heal them.

544
00:42:00,800 --> 00:42:03,300
That way, I can save on compensation and medical fees.

545
00:42:03,300 --> 00:42:05,726
What kind of twisted logic is that?

546
00:42:06,816 --> 00:42:08,342
You actually came back to Kinmen
to run a guesthouse

547
00:42:08,342 --> 00:42:11,300
after finishing university in Taipei.

548
00:42:11,300 --> 00:42:14,092
I'm not just saying that.

549
00:42:14,092 --> 00:42:17,309
If I say it, I'll do it.

550
00:42:18,299 --> 00:42:19,365
Running a guesthouse...

551
00:42:19,365 --> 00:42:22,100
You just want to stay close to your grandma, right?

552
00:42:23,134 --> 00:42:26,976
Yes, because I want to be her bodyguard.

553
00:42:27,602 --> 00:42:29,842
- Nice.
- What about you?

554
00:42:29,842 --> 00:42:31,641
I'm more interested in hearing your story.

555
00:42:31,641 --> 00:42:33,399
You have been to so many places.

556
00:42:33,399 --> 00:42:35,425
How do you feel about that?

557
00:42:35,425 --> 00:42:37,774
How do I feel?

558
00:42:37,774 --> 00:42:39,733
Not much.

559
00:42:39,733 --> 00:42:44,299
I've seen and experienced a lot outside. I gained a lot of insight.

560
00:42:44,299 --> 00:42:46,684
Now, I just want to come back to Kinmen.

561
00:42:49,051 --> 00:42:51,018
Because you're here.

562
00:42:55,176 --> 00:42:56,642
Me?
